    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix 64QAM LLR computation for FeMBMS 1.25KHz carrier spacing\n\n### Summary\nThere's a critical bug in the 64QAM LLR computation functions for both regular and 1.25KHz spacing that causes incomplete processing of input data. This results in corrupted or missing LLR values for certain PMCH configurations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/pmch_ue.c`: Fixed incorrect loop count calculation in both `mch_64qam_llr()` and `mch_64qam_llr_khz_1dot25()` functions.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running PMCH decoding with 64QAM modulation and specific resource block configurations where the total number of REs is not divisible by 4, users observe:\n- Incomplete LLR arrays with missing values at the end\n- Incorrect decoding performance for high MCS values\n- Potential memory access issues when downstream processing expects fully populated LLR arrays\n\nThe issue manifests most clearly when:\n1. Using 64QAM modulation on PMCH\n2. With a number of resource elements that leaves a remainder when divided by 4\n3. In both normal and 1.25KHz carrier spacing modes\n\nThis causes the last 1-3 REs worth of LLR values to be omitted from processing, leading to degraded performance or decoding failures.\n"
}